	The candidate has the opportunity to gain hands-on experience at a cause-based technology company, working directly with the nonprofit resource relations department. Causecast provides nonprofits with free technology and resources to activate supporters, maximize efficiency and promote their causes.<br />
	<br />
	<strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br />
	<br />
	The internship incorporates writing, research, media relations support, social media outreach, updating contact databases, etc. Specifically, interns will:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Assist in managing relationships with both prospective and member nonprofit organizations</li>
	<li>
		Propose, research and assist in the development of viral marketing strategies primarily via social media</li>
	<li>
		Assist in the research, development and implementation of campaigns to promote the news and stories of member organizations</li>
	<li>
		Propose, research and assist in partnership formation to increase the distribution of the news and stories for member organizations</li>
	<li>
		Day-to-day management and expansion of the department&#39;s social media properties</li>
	<li>
		Assist in managing contact databases of current and prospective nonprofit organizations</li>
	<li>
		Assist in the writing of press releases and related content for the department&#39;s e-newsletter</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<br />
	<strong>Required Skills and Experience: </strong><br />
	<br />
	Strong interest in nonprofit relations, technology, social media and to further pursue a career in the fields noted above.</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Excellent written communication and research skills are a must</li>
	<li>
		Computer experience in Google Docs and Mac OSX</li>
	<li>
		Good organizational skills and attention to details and deadlines</li>
	<li>
		Enthusiastic and eager to learn</li>
	<li>
		Ability to work independently, act proactively and take initiativeProfessional, ability to multi-task, flexible, accuracy and thoroughness are especially important</li>
	<li>
		Background in communications (PR/Marketing), with experience in social media engagement, preferred</li>
</ul>
<p>
	Must be enthusiastic about working in a fast-paced start-up environment. If you are a passionate, cause-oriented individual, we welcome your contribution.</p>
<p>
	<br />
