			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Causecast is looking for a hands-on&nbsp; to join our team of passionate and talented individuals dedicated to helping nonprofits and businesses champion the causes they care about.<br />
	<br />
	We are looking for someone with expert knowledge of user-centered interface design, UX competencies,&nbsp; methodologies and user research and testing.<br />
	<br />
	The Information Architect needs to have working knowledge of web based software used for user interface design and documentation.<br />
	<br />
	<strong>Responsibilities include (but not limited to):</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Information Architecture</li>
	<li>
		Rapid Prototyping</li>
	<li>
		Usability Testing and Research</li>
	<li>
		Wire Framing</li>
	<li>
		Site Flows</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<br />
	<strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Candidate must have 5+ years experience in Information Architecture design</li>
	<li>
		Candidate must have a strong portfolio of wireframes created for a variety of interactive experiences including websites, applications and mobile devices.</li>
	<li>
		Candidate must have experience creating Personas</li>
	<li>
		Candidate must have conducted user-testing</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<br />
	<strong>ABOUT US</strong><br />
	<br />
	Causecast (www.causecast.org) is a full-service cause integration company that works with some of the world&#39;s leading entertainment platforms, nonprofits, celebrities, and brands. Merging the power of storytelling, technology, and the modern media mix we&#39;ve developed a platform to turn interest into action and action into impact. This platform focus on three goals: to inspire people with great content, to engage them with clear calls to action, and to measure and report the impact of that action.<br />
	<br />
	Causecast is growing and we are looking for people who can grow with so this position presents a tremendous opportunity for the right candidate. You will be working with a team of hard working, incredibly dedicated and cause-minded individuals; it&#39;s a great place to put your skills to work and know that your work is making an impact.</p>
